This is a repository of publically released pieces of the App Inventor
for Android project.  

Contents:

+ jars/libSimpleAndroidRuntime.jar
    A Jar containing a version of App Inventor's Android runtime
    library.  This library jar file can be used to build Android apps
    in Java that make use of the App Inventor components.

+ samples/HelloHappyFace/
    A sample Android source tree for a simple Android app that uses
    App Inventor components.

+ samples/AppInventorInJavaSample/
    A more extensive sample of using App Inventor components in a
    standard Android Java program.  Includes a simple new component
    definition.

+ src/components
    The source code to the App Inventor components.  This is the
    component code that is compiled into the
    jars/libSimpleAndroidRuntime.jar mentioned above.  This code is
    provided mostly for use in understanding the App Inventor
    component architecture and is intended be useful for folks wanting
    to write their own components.